analyzed_images.image_description: The image is a map of the VATSIM Germany Sektor Bottrop (EDDL_BOT_APP) used for flight simulation purposes. The map outlines various airspace sectors with their respective radio frequencies and altitude limits. The central sector, labeled BOT7, has a frequency of 245 and altitude limits of 155. Surrounding sectors include BOT1, BOT2, BOT3, BOT4, BOT5, BOT6, and others, each with specific frequencies and altitude limits. The map also includes adjacent sectors such as EHAA CTA E2, EHMC TMA E, HMM1, HMM2, PADH1, and DUS52, among others. The map is intended for simulation use only and is not to be used for real-world flight.

The image is a map of the FIR (Flight Information Region) Langen, dated 07.01.2022, created by VACC Germany. The map outlines various sectors within the FIR, each labeled with identifiers and altitude limits. 

Key features include:
- The central area highlighted in orange, which encompasses sectors DU51, DU52, DU53, DU54, DU55, DU56, and DU57. These sectors have altitude limits ranging from ground level (GND) to 245.
- Surrounding sectors include BOT1, BOT2, BOT3, BOT4, BOT5, BOT6, NOR1, NOR2, DKA1, DKA2, DKA3, TAU1, SIG1, PADH1, PADH2, PADL1, PADL2, PADL3, PADL4, and HMM1. Each sector has specific altitude limits indicated next to their identifiers.
- The map is bordered by a thick black line, indicating the boundary of the FIR Langen.

The map is used for air traffic control and navigation purposes, providing a clear depiction of the different controlled airspaces within the FIR.

metadata.abstract: The document 'EBG 1 BOT DUS' provides detailed information for flight simulator use, specifically for the Bottrop (EDDL BOT APP) and Düsseldorf Terminal (EDDL APP) sectors within the Langen FIR. It includes sector boundaries, altitudes, and frequencies for various areas such as EHMC TMA E, EHAA CTA E2, and TEBRO AREA. The document outlines the main sector tasks for EDDL arrivals and departures, as well as traffic management for EDLV and ETNG. Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for both sectors are mentioned, with links to detailed SOPs for EDDL arrivals. The document also provides login details, sector indicators, frequencies, and callsigns for controllers operating in these sectors. It emphasizes that the information is for flight simulator use only and not for real-world flight operations.
